WEBVTT

00:54.827 --> 00:57.246
EPISODE 2

01:15.264 --> 01:16.932
TRANQUILIZER

01:26.191 --> 01:27.401
DO EUN-HYUK

01:28.944 --> 01:29.820
Hello?

01:30.696 --> 01:31.572
Seol-ah.

01:33.574 --> 01:34.408
Where are you right now?

01:35.284 --> 01:36.452
Why?

01:38.037 --> 01:38.996
Seung-jae…

01:42.082 --> 01:43.250
was in an accident.

01:45.419 --> 01:47.004
Can you come to the dock right now?

01:58.766 --> 02:00.434
I think someone died.

02:00.517 --> 02:01.477
Oh, no.

02:38.764 --> 02:40.015
It's him.

02:45.020 --> 02:46.063
He was my fiancé.

02:47.982 --> 02:48.941
Did you already know?

02:49.441 --> 02:52.236
That he canceled his policy
before he died?

02:53.070 --> 02:53.904
Yes.

02:56.782 --> 02:57.700
What a shame.

02:57.783 --> 02:59.618
If he hadn't canceled it,

03:00.285 --> 03:02.538
you could've held 700 million won
in your hands.

03:02.621 --> 03:04.164
You must have a lot of time on your hands

03:05.332 --> 03:07.584
to investigate a canceled policy.

03:08.711 --> 03:10.129
You couldn't receive the death benefit,

03:10.713 --> 03:14.133
but the 200 million won premium
was returned to Mr. Yoon's account.

03:14.925 --> 03:17.636
And you're assuming
that money came my way?

03:19.555 --> 03:22.975
You think I killed my fiancé
for a measly 200 million won?

03:25.477 --> 03:26.895
Tell me.

03:26.979 --> 03:30.941
What does his accident
have to do with what happened to Ms. Kim?

03:39.116 --> 03:40.576
I can smell it.

03:42.786 --> 03:43.912
The stench of someone…

03:46.248 --> 03:47.958
trading human lives for money.

03:51.336 --> 03:52.379
Seol-ah.

03:56.091 --> 03:57.384
What are you doing?

03:57.468 --> 03:58.385
Who are you?

03:59.219 --> 04:00.721
You're the one who interrupted us.

04:00.804 --> 04:02.473
Who do you think you are
to treat Seol-ah--

04:02.556 --> 04:03.390
Don't.

04:08.687 --> 04:10.981
Do you, by any chance,
know Mr. Yoon Seung-jae as well?

04:11.774 --> 04:14.526
I'd like to talk to you.
Can I get your contact number?

04:20.407 --> 04:21.825
I'll give you my business card, then.

04:28.373 --> 04:29.333
I'll be waiting.

04:57.069 --> 04:58.237
You didn't eat again, did you?

04:58.987 --> 04:59.905
Give me a minute.

05:05.077 --> 05:06.912
NONGHYUP LIFE INSURANCE
SIU SENIOR MANAGER CHA WOO-SEOK

05:09.123 --> 05:11.333
Why did an SIU investigator
come to see you?

05:12.793 --> 05:14.002
And what was all that about Seung-jae?

05:15.003 --> 05:18.298
It seems Kim Yun-ji and Seung-jae
had insurance with that company.

05:19.258 --> 05:20.384
Insurance?

05:28.142 --> 05:28.976
"Seiren"?

05:29.560 --> 05:32.896
You know, mermaids that lured sailors
with their singing.

05:34.398 --> 05:36.650
Oh, I think I remember that
from Greek mythology.

05:38.902 --> 05:40.362
I found that story amusing.

05:40.946 --> 05:42.406
I wonder why those men

05:42.489 --> 05:45.284
jumped into the water despite knowing
it'd lead to their deaths.

05:48.120 --> 05:49.121
Is that why

05:49.204 --> 05:50.998
you made it your restaurant logo?

05:52.040 --> 05:53.041
Yeah.

06:02.801 --> 06:05.888
Seol-ah doesn't fully open herself.

06:09.183 --> 06:13.187
There are times when she feels unfamiliar,
as if I'm seeing her for the first time,

06:13.937 --> 06:15.606
and as if she could vanish one day.

06:21.528 --> 06:22.362
Seung-jae…

06:24.573 --> 06:27.492
are you still worried
she won't accept your proposal?

06:30.287 --> 06:31.121
Actually…

06:32.831 --> 06:34.958
I took out a life insurance policy
with Seol-ah as the beneficiary.

06:48.513 --> 06:49.932
EUN-HYE

07:34.518 --> 07:36.019
KIM YUN-JI
AUCTIONEER AT ROYAL AUCTION

07:36.103 --> 07:38.438
DATE OF DEATH: AUGUST 26, 2025
POLICY ISSUE DATE: AUGUST 10, 2023

07:38.522 --> 07:40.649
PUSHED? ACCIDENT? SUICIDE?
TIP CALL BEFORE DEATH

07:42.192 --> 07:45.946
What does his accident
have to do with what happened to Yun-ji?

07:46.029 --> 07:47.739
YOON SEUNG-JAE, OWNER OF THE GALLERY
DATE OF DEATH: AUGUST 17, 2025

07:47.823 --> 07:49.533
BENEFICIARY: HAN SEOL-AH
CHEONGYANG RIVER YACHT ACCIDENT: DROWNED?

07:52.286 --> 07:54.788
And you're assuming
that money came my way?

07:56.915 --> 08:00.544
You think I killed my fiancé
for a measly 200 million won?

08:18.103 --> 08:19.938
These are the newly arrived pieces.

08:24.192 --> 08:25.861
And the condition report for these?

08:25.944 --> 08:28.322
I found the file on Ms. Kim's computer.

08:28.405 --> 08:29.531
I'll take care of it.

08:29.614 --> 08:31.867
I appreciate it, Sang-mi.

08:31.950 --> 08:32.784
Of course.

08:33.368 --> 08:34.244
Also,

08:34.828 --> 08:35.912
about that…

08:38.206 --> 08:39.207
What should we do with it?

08:42.127 --> 08:43.670
COMMUNITY CHAT SEARCH
RISK LIFE FOR MONEY

08:43.754 --> 08:45.464
Anyone willing to risk their life
for money?

08:46.757 --> 08:47.799
Must be in Cheongun.

08:47.883 --> 08:50.594
Recruiting a hitter
with a clean insurance record.

08:51.470 --> 08:52.554
What's the rate?

08:53.347 --> 08:55.140
If we go easy,
about three million won per person.

08:56.350 --> 08:57.225
I'm in.

08:57.976 --> 08:58.977
What car do you have?

08:59.061 --> 09:00.687
It's less suspicious if it's expensive.

09:04.232 --> 09:05.734
It's a foreign-made car, of course.

09:06.568 --> 09:08.987
Yes, I'll get back to you shortly.

09:10.655 --> 09:12.366
-Mr. Cha.
-Yeah?

09:12.449 --> 09:15.494
Ms. Kim Yun-ji's family
had no idea about her insurance policy.

09:23.585 --> 09:25.128
Take all the time you need.

09:26.630 --> 09:27.506
Once you get in touch,

09:28.173 --> 09:30.801
I'll make sure the insurance payout
is processed smoothly.

09:33.095 --> 09:34.262
Thank you.

09:35.347 --> 09:36.431
Thank you, but…

09:37.724 --> 09:40.102
I'd pay a hundred times that amount

09:41.520 --> 09:43.647
if it'd bring my child back.

09:44.523 --> 09:46.775
My precious daughter is gone.

09:47.484 --> 09:49.444
What's the point of any of this?

10:08.171 --> 10:09.089
I'll take that.

10:10.132 --> 10:11.591
It's heavy.

10:11.675 --> 10:12.801
I'm sorry for the trouble.

10:14.094 --> 10:15.178
Let me carry it for you.

10:19.141 --> 10:20.642
He's from the insurance company.

10:22.936 --> 10:23.812
Where should I put it?

10:24.396 --> 10:25.313
This way, please.

10:40.996 --> 10:42.914
It feels like she'll be back any moment,

10:43.748 --> 10:45.250
so I left everything just as it is.

10:46.543 --> 10:47.502
Over here, please.

10:56.219 --> 10:58.430
There are a lot of company documents.

10:58.513 --> 11:01.016
You can take them with you
if you need them.

11:01.933 --> 11:03.435
Okay, I will.

11:04.394 --> 11:05.395
All right, then.

11:06.062 --> 11:07.189
Take a look around.

11:08.899 --> 11:11.067
I'll prepare some tea for you
in the living room.

11:54.236 --> 11:55.820
H2 2025 GLOBAL ART TRENDS REPORT

12:29.187 --> 12:30.897
Can you step out for a bit?

12:32.023 --> 12:32.857
Why?

12:32.941 --> 12:34.985
Do you want to rummage on your own?

12:35.068 --> 12:36.695
Didn't you hear what her mother said?

12:37.404 --> 12:39.239
She told me to take the company documents.

12:59.801 --> 13:02.679
HAN SEOL-AH BUSINESS TRIP

13:02.762 --> 13:04.681
HAN SEOL-AH MEETING
WITH SU GALLERY MANAGER

13:06.391 --> 13:08.768
HAN SEOL-AH ON LEAVE

13:11.438 --> 13:13.481
OUT OF THE OFFICE ALL DAY
MAYBE A VIP CLIENT MEETING?

13:21.656 --> 13:24.826
She didn't smile once
after joining Royal Auction.

13:25.660 --> 13:27.120
I thought it was rather strange

13:27.203 --> 13:29.831
when she left the TV station

13:29.914 --> 13:32.125
and suddenly decided to work
at an auction house.

13:35.545 --> 13:36.755
What kind of person

13:37.922 --> 13:39.591
was Ms. Kim at work?

13:45.597 --> 13:47.265
She was hard-working.

13:48.975 --> 13:50.727
I heard she was about to get promoted.

13:52.270 --> 13:53.563
I just don't understand.

13:54.105 --> 13:56.232
When a suicide takes place at a company,

13:57.400 --> 13:58.652
there's usually a message behind it.

13:59.527 --> 14:02.781
For example, workplace bullying,
conflict between colleagues,

14:02.864 --> 14:03.698
or being wronged.

14:03.782 --> 14:05.825
But you're saying
it was none of these things.

14:06.409 --> 14:07.786
Then I wonder what it was.

14:08.912 --> 14:10.997
I don't know
everyone's personal matters at work.

14:15.043 --> 14:18.213
Do you have any idea
what it could've been?

14:19.923 --> 14:20.757
There's one thing…

14:22.884 --> 14:24.427
that comes to mind.

14:37.399 --> 14:39.901
Why are you out all night these days?

14:40.944 --> 14:43.405
Get up and have a bite to eat
before you sleep.

14:55.959 --> 14:56.835
Are you…

14:58.086 --> 14:59.713
seeing that man again?

15:01.589 --> 15:02.924
Were you with him?

15:05.009 --> 15:07.220
What's wrong, Yun-ji?

15:11.850 --> 15:14.686
Do you know the man Yun-ji was seeing?

15:19.691 --> 15:20.984
A man?

15:21.693 --> 15:23.737
I'm her mother, but I don't know anything.

15:26.489 --> 15:28.491
I don't know why
she was suffering so much,

15:29.242 --> 15:31.786
or why she chose to end things.

15:31.870 --> 15:33.079
ASSOCIATE AUCTIONEER KIM YUN-JI

15:33.163 --> 15:36.916
I'm her mother, but I don't know anything.

15:43.006 --> 15:44.924
I'm sure you went through
everything at work.

15:47.010 --> 15:49.304
Did you come to check
if she left something at home?

15:49.888 --> 15:51.473
You came to check first,

15:51.556 --> 15:52.807
but I guess you didn't find anything.

15:53.391 --> 15:54.851
You want to know what I found?

15:55.769 --> 15:56.770
I could tell you.

15:57.395 --> 15:58.730
Keep it to yourself.

15:58.813 --> 16:01.065
I don't care what you came here to do,

16:01.149 --> 16:04.486
but I find it offensive to be questioned
before a mother who lost her daughter.

16:04.569 --> 16:06.988
Shouldn't you be more cooperative
as her immediate supervisor?

16:07.071 --> 16:09.574
I've already cooperated with the police.

16:09.657 --> 16:11.743
And I have no interest
in prying into the private life

16:12.285 --> 16:13.244
of the deceased.

16:14.037 --> 16:15.789
I'm trying to find out

16:17.248 --> 16:18.833
whether or not it was a wrongful death.

16:20.710 --> 16:21.795
Wrongful death?

16:25.924 --> 16:27.091
What about wrongful suspicion?

16:28.843 --> 16:31.679
You never know
who the real victim might be.

17:10.134 --> 17:12.470
VIOLENT CRIMES UNIT 1

17:13.930 --> 17:14.973
CALL LOG
NAME: KIM YUN-JI

17:16.683 --> 17:18.434
YOON SEUNG-JAE

17:19.018 --> 17:20.395
YOON SEUNG-JAE

17:25.024 --> 17:26.150
Yoon Seung-jae.

17:26.776 --> 17:27.902
Yoon Seung-jae.

17:28.611 --> 17:29.821
Yoon Seung-jae again.

17:31.823 --> 17:34.033
Hey, Ggong.
You've heard of Yoon Seung-jae, right?

17:34.117 --> 17:37.120
Yes, I left the Cheongun Police Station
investigation report on your desk.

17:37.662 --> 17:38.663
Investigation report?

17:40.915 --> 17:42.917
GANGNAM "A CLUB" VIP NARCOTICS CASE
GANGHA POLICE STATION

17:45.753 --> 17:49.173
YOON SEUNG-JAE DEATH CASE

17:52.594 --> 17:56.389
BODY FOUND FLOATING IN WATER
BODY IDENTIFIED BY FIANCÉE (HAN SEOL-AH)

18:09.319 --> 18:11.529
NONGHYUP LIFE INSURANCE

18:11.613 --> 18:13.948
2025 CERTIFIED
INSURANCE FRAUD INVESTIGATOR

18:19.579 --> 18:21.831
Don't tell me he hasn't come to work yet.

18:22.373 --> 18:24.626
Does he not know the quarter-end
is right around the corner?

18:25.209 --> 18:26.586
That little punk.

18:27.170 --> 18:28.171
Hey, Cha.

18:29.047 --> 18:30.214
Where the hell are you?!

18:32.800 --> 18:34.052
Oh, I see.

18:34.135 --> 18:36.512
Of course, you have to spend money.

18:37.764 --> 18:39.474
Right, right. Be careful, okay?

18:40.850 --> 18:41.684
What did he say?

18:41.768 --> 18:43.227
He's bringing in a big one.

18:46.439 --> 18:49.233
I'm so done being stuck in this office.

18:49.317 --> 18:50.735
I'm getting out of here!

18:50.818 --> 18:51.653
I can do this!

18:53.154 --> 18:54.238
"The Purpose of Insurance."

19:04.832 --> 19:09.754
CHEONGUN, WHERE LIFE IS GOOD

19:09.837 --> 19:11.714
All right, the backers are here and ready.

19:11.798 --> 19:12.632
Where are you, Mr. Hitter?

19:13.341 --> 19:15.009
I'm 500 meters behind.

19:15.551 --> 19:16.719
This is your first time, right?

19:16.803 --> 19:19.347
I'll go straight,
then turn right, and brake hard,

19:19.430 --> 19:21.140
so be bold and don't hold back.

19:21.224 --> 19:22.517
Just ram into us, okay?

19:23.977 --> 19:25.603
But you're in a compact car.

19:25.687 --> 19:28.564
Just go for it. We won't die.

19:29.816 --> 19:31.985
I'll hit you full force, then.

19:32.068 --> 19:32.944
Okay.

19:33.569 --> 19:34.696
What's your plate number again?

19:35.279 --> 19:36.364
It's 7622.

19:36.447 --> 19:38.199
Got it.

19:38.282 --> 19:39.450
Follow us, but don't make it obvious.

19:39.993 --> 19:41.077
Hey, let's go.

19:54.340 --> 19:55.883
What's taking him so long?

19:57.552 --> 19:59.929
Damn it, why isn't Cha Woo-seok here yet?

20:01.014 --> 20:04.600
-Hey, move over, will you?
-Sit still, for crying out loud.

20:04.684 --> 20:06.144
-Why isn't he coming?
-Why is it so tight in here?

20:06.227 --> 20:07.603
Where is he?

20:08.187 --> 20:10.314
Hey, where are you?
You said you had a foreign-made car.

20:10.898 --> 20:12.233
I do.

20:12.316 --> 20:13.985
It's just a bit big.

20:14.068 --> 20:15.403
What the hell are you saying?

20:29.000 --> 20:30.460
What the hell? It's 7622!

20:32.211 --> 20:33.129
That's him!

20:33.212 --> 20:35.339
-Hey, step on it!
-What the hell?

20:35.923 --> 20:37.467
What the hell is with him?

20:37.550 --> 20:39.177
-Just go!
-Go!

20:39.260 --> 20:40.595
-Speed it up!
-Step on it!

20:42.096 --> 20:43.639
Go faster!

20:44.182 --> 20:45.767
Step on it already!

20:45.850 --> 20:47.643
I told you to lose some weight!

20:47.727 --> 20:49.687
-He's going to hit us!
-Go, go, go!

20:52.273 --> 20:53.983
Hey, move to the side!

20:55.026 --> 20:56.444
I told you to lose some weight, idiot!

20:56.527 --> 20:57.403
Hey!

20:57.487 --> 20:59.614
You crazy bastard! Stop right now!

21:00.114 --> 21:01.949
-Hey!
-Step on it!

21:02.033 --> 21:03.326
He's closing in!

21:03.409 --> 21:05.495
-Go faster!
-He's going to hit us!

21:07.622 --> 21:09.624
Go faster, come on!

21:09.707 --> 21:11.334
Speed up!

21:11.417 --> 21:12.627
Step on it!

21:14.670 --> 21:16.422
-Go faster!
-He's coming!

21:17.715 --> 21:18.549
Step on it!

21:20.927 --> 21:23.137
This is my goddamn car!

21:25.014 --> 21:26.641
-Watch it!
-Holy crap!

21:32.146 --> 21:33.231
Oh, jeez.

21:39.821 --> 21:40.905
Damn it.

21:42.990 --> 21:44.575
Man, I feel like I'm going to die.

21:44.659 --> 21:46.327
Oh, man.

21:46.410 --> 21:47.662
What are you all looking at?

21:51.499 --> 21:53.084
It's nothing. Go back inside.

21:54.460 --> 21:55.586
Oh, dear.

21:55.670 --> 21:57.171
I was going to hit you from behind,

21:57.255 --> 21:59.132
but you crashed into the truck
in front of you.

21:59.215 --> 22:00.299
Hey.

22:00.383 --> 22:02.093
Were you trying to kill or something?

22:02.176 --> 22:03.136
Yeah.

22:03.219 --> 22:05.304
-How'd you know?
-Hey.

22:05.888 --> 22:06.764
Hey.

22:06.848 --> 22:08.808
Oh, let me introduce you to each other.

22:09.475 --> 22:12.311
This is Detective Kim
from Cheongun Police Station.

22:12.395 --> 22:14.939
And this is the Cheongun Family Gang,

22:15.022 --> 22:16.315
an insurance fraud ring.

22:16.899 --> 22:18.192
Oh, I see.

22:20.194 --> 22:21.320
An insurance fraud ring, huh?

22:21.404 --> 22:23.614
-Cops?
-Nice to meet you.

22:23.698 --> 22:26.534
-All right, let's go.
-That hurts!

22:28.494 --> 22:30.955
-Come on.
-That hurts!

22:31.038 --> 22:33.082
-See you.
-Go already.

22:34.292 --> 22:35.877
No wonder you wanted to meet

22:35.960 --> 22:37.962
at such a random place
instead of the station.

22:41.215 --> 22:42.049
Here.

22:44.177 --> 22:45.720
Files on all the scams
they've pulled off so far

22:45.803 --> 22:47.263
and CCTV footage.

22:47.346 --> 22:48.514
Man.

22:48.598 --> 22:49.640
This is just what I needed.

22:49.724 --> 22:51.601
A guy like you
should've stayed on as a detective.

22:53.352 --> 22:55.062
Let me show you
what you asked me to look into.

22:56.522 --> 22:59.108
When I got there, he was already dead.

22:59.817 --> 23:00.818
It was an accidental death.

23:01.861 --> 23:04.030
Are you sure Yoon Seung-jae
was alone on the yacht?

23:04.113 --> 23:04.947
Yeah.

23:05.031 --> 23:08.784
There were a lot of witnesses,
including the dock manager and fishermen.

23:09.994 --> 23:11.996
-Then the autopsy results must also--
-Death by drowning.

23:12.622 --> 23:15.583
I think he accidentally fell overboard
and struck the propellers.

23:16.959 --> 23:18.836
The case itself isn't strange,

23:18.920 --> 23:20.296
but that woman was a bit…

23:22.256 --> 23:23.299
Here it is.

23:25.801 --> 23:28.763
His family was overseas at the time,

23:28.846 --> 23:31.015
so his fiancée came to identify the body.

23:32.683 --> 23:35.228
I worried she might pass out
because the body was severely damaged,

23:35.311 --> 23:36.896
but she didn't even bat an eye.

24:33.536 --> 24:34.370
Here.

24:35.579 --> 24:37.290
I canceled the insurance policy,

24:37.873 --> 24:38.874
so don't worry.

25:03.274 --> 25:05.901
CHAIR KIM

25:07.486 --> 25:08.321
I always make sure

25:09.322 --> 25:13.159
to include steamed sea bream
on my father's ancestral table.

25:13.909 --> 25:15.244
He must've liked it.

25:16.162 --> 25:17.621
He didn't because it was too fishy.

25:17.705 --> 25:19.332
I only make it because I want to eat it.

25:22.209 --> 25:23.044
Try some.

25:24.462 --> 25:26.547
Are you sure you didn't make it for me?

25:27.757 --> 25:29.175
Sharp as ever.

25:30.051 --> 25:33.679
Back when I used to bring raw fish
to Artist Han's studio,

25:33.763 --> 25:35.681
you were always the most excited.

25:35.765 --> 25:39.435
Even at a young age, you ate everything,
including sea squirt and sea cucumber.

25:41.187 --> 25:42.646
You seem to remember everything.

25:43.898 --> 25:46.108
You made the right call
visiting Ms. Kim's family.

25:47.443 --> 25:50.321
It takes that kind of thinking
to protect a company.

25:50.988 --> 25:54.909
Workplace bullying
is such a big topic these days.

25:56.285 --> 25:58.454
-How did you--
-They called to say thank you.

25:59.038 --> 26:01.582
Did you know her father
works at the National Tax Service?

26:01.665 --> 26:05.169
If he set his mind to it,
he could easily take down our company.

26:07.797 --> 26:10.716
From what I've heard, her death seems to
have been caused by personal matters.

26:10.800 --> 26:13.719
Her mother didn't harbor
any resentment toward us.

26:13.803 --> 26:16.347
She appeared to be having
a hard time though.

26:17.139 --> 26:18.641
You're having a hard time too.

26:19.642 --> 26:21.268
I heard you lost your fiancé
in an accident.

26:21.852 --> 26:23.187
If something like that happened,

26:23.854 --> 26:26.399
you should've told me
and taken some time off.

26:28.818 --> 26:31.904
It was better for me to focus on work.

26:35.241 --> 26:36.450
You poor thing.

26:41.205 --> 26:43.624
Here, eat up while it's still warm.

27:47.480 --> 27:50.274
I called you earlier.
I'm Cha Woo-seok, an SIU investigator.

27:51.525 --> 27:52.776
What is this about?

27:52.860 --> 27:55.488
I'm investigating matters
involving Mr. Yoon Seung-jae's insurance.

27:56.906 --> 27:58.449
I believe he had a fiancée?

27:59.825 --> 28:00.701
Yes, I know her.

28:01.410 --> 28:02.453
Seol-ah.

28:03.621 --> 28:04.622
Do you happen to know

28:05.456 --> 28:06.916
Ms. Kim Yun-ji as well?

28:08.000 --> 28:08.876
Who?

28:12.796 --> 28:13.631
This person.

28:15.007 --> 28:16.133
Oh, I've seen her before.

28:16.217 --> 28:18.177
I remember her
because she's been coming by often.

28:19.011 --> 28:20.888
Ms. Kim Yun-ji has been here?

28:20.971 --> 28:22.014
What for?

28:22.097 --> 28:23.849
I wouldn't know.

28:28.812 --> 28:30.940
What was her relationship with Mr. Yoon?

28:31.023 --> 28:32.816
Did it look like
they'd known each other long?

28:32.900 --> 28:34.818
They didn't seem close.

28:34.902 --> 28:37.446
Mr. Yoon didn't seem that fond of her.

28:39.365 --> 28:40.533
When was her last visit?

28:42.368 --> 28:44.495
The day before Mr. Yoon's accident.

28:44.578 --> 28:46.539
She came by again

28:46.622 --> 28:49.833
and waited until we closed,
saying she had something to tell him.

28:53.212 --> 28:54.213
She sat over there.

30:12.916 --> 30:15.961
When I got there, he was already dead.

30:16.045 --> 30:17.338
It was an accidental death.

30:38.692 --> 30:41.320
Kim Yun-ji and Yoon Seung-jae met,

30:42.488 --> 30:44.156
and they both died

30:45.658 --> 30:46.825
in just ten days.

30:49.745 --> 30:51.455
I didn't know you were so competent.

30:54.333 --> 30:56.377
It's normal for the police
to have reasonable suspicions.

30:56.877 --> 30:58.212
But why would an SIU investigator

30:58.754 --> 31:01.256
chase after a case
where a payout was never made?

31:03.258 --> 31:04.635
That's the problem with you, Seong-il.

31:05.511 --> 31:07.012
You lack imagination.

31:08.138 --> 31:09.264
You think this was the first time?

31:10.307 --> 31:11.850
This is why you're always one step behind.

31:14.228 --> 31:16.563
Ever thought that your imagination
might be the problem?

31:17.147 --> 31:18.899
Like the delusion
about your sister's death

31:19.733 --> 31:20.567
being a murder.

31:23.821 --> 31:26.281
As the detective in charge,
you don't want to admit incompetence,

31:26.365 --> 31:27.616
yet you want peace of mind.

31:28.909 --> 31:29.743
Yeah.

31:30.577 --> 31:31.704
I get it.

31:33.038 --> 31:34.206
But are you really at peace?

32:05.821 --> 32:07.114
What are you thinking about?

32:08.407 --> 32:10.284
Stop worrying about me.

32:10.367 --> 32:11.493
I'm not.

32:11.577 --> 32:13.787
You are. It's written all over your face.

32:13.871 --> 32:16.039
I didn't lie like my friends did

32:16.123 --> 32:17.875
and was honest about
taking a trip with my boyfriend.

32:19.668 --> 32:21.712
Jeez, when did you grow up?

32:21.795 --> 32:23.213
I think I'll get married before you.

32:26.008 --> 32:27.050
Ms. Cha Woo-hee.

32:27.718 --> 32:29.595
Marriage already? Control yourself.

33:16.600 --> 33:17.768
I'll have what she's having.

33:43.001 --> 33:45.712
Did you know Kim Yun-ji went to see
Yoon Seung-jae at his restaurant?

33:48.382 --> 33:49.633
On the day before the accident, at that.

33:53.804 --> 33:54.930
So?

33:56.890 --> 33:58.225
Why did those two meet?

34:00.936 --> 34:03.480
You can't know everything about someone,
no matter how close you are to them.

34:06.233 --> 34:07.568
So you have no idea?

34:09.653 --> 34:11.154
Then what could it be?

34:12.239 --> 34:15.993
What reason was there for your fiancé
and colleague to meet secretly?

34:17.828 --> 34:19.913
It didn't seem like
they were just acquaintances.

34:21.582 --> 34:22.583
Were they

34:23.709 --> 34:25.586
involved or something?

34:35.637 --> 34:37.055
You kill out of love,

34:37.764 --> 34:40.767
you kill out of hate, and you want to kill
as much as you love.

34:42.978 --> 34:45.063
The most common motive for murder
is love affairs.

34:47.900 --> 34:48.734
Love affairs?

34:50.027 --> 34:51.153
Not a fan of that theory?

34:51.737 --> 34:53.697
Then what about
premeditated murder for money?

34:58.660 --> 35:00.996
Do you know what insurance scammers
have in common?

35:02.706 --> 35:04.875
Once they've had a taste of money,
they want more.

35:04.958 --> 35:07.044
They want bigger money
through easier means.

35:07.127 --> 35:10.714
Then things escalate, and they get bolder,
so bold that people start to notice.

35:13.008 --> 35:14.968
-What does that have to do with--
-Ms. Han Seol-ah.

35:16.720 --> 35:18.096
I'm investigating a tip I received.

35:19.348 --> 35:22.476
A tip claiming that Yoon Seung-jae's death
was a case of murder-for-insurance.

35:28.857 --> 35:30.400
I see Ms. Kim Yun-ji gave you the tip.

35:31.693 --> 35:33.278
I was supposed to meet her that night.

35:34.571 --> 35:35.530
But she goes and commits suicide?

35:38.075 --> 35:39.326
That makes no sense at all.

35:43.246 --> 35:44.790
Stop playing detective.

35:46.041 --> 35:48.377
I never received any insurance payout,

35:48.460 --> 35:49.294
which means

35:50.504 --> 35:52.422
I'm not the subject of your investigation.

35:54.967 --> 35:56.301
I guess I'll find the answer
if I dig deeper.

35:59.972 --> 36:01.556
What is it that you really want to know?

36:05.894 --> 36:07.938
Your fiancé and Kim Yun-ji.

36:12.818 --> 36:13.819
Did you kill them?

37:16.339 --> 37:20.135
HAN SEOL-AH IN CHEONGUN CITY

37:24.931 --> 37:27.851
HAN SEOL-AH, KIM YUN-JI, YOON SEUNG-JAE

37:28.435 --> 37:29.478
A love triangle?

37:29.561 --> 37:30.812
I don't think Han Seol-ah knew.

37:32.856 --> 37:33.732
Really?

37:34.524 --> 37:35.734
Micro expressions.

37:37.694 --> 37:39.279
No matter how good your poker face is,

37:39.905 --> 37:42.157
you can't hide fleeting expressions.

37:43.825 --> 37:44.785
She didn't know.

37:46.995 --> 37:49.414
And there's no way to find out
since they're both dead.

37:50.332 --> 37:51.458
What really happened?

37:52.876 --> 37:53.919
But you know,

37:55.003 --> 37:57.756
when I asked if she killed them,
she was surprisingly unshaken.

37:58.340 --> 37:59.257
It's one or the other.

38:00.383 --> 38:01.426
Either she's innocent,

38:02.010 --> 38:03.970
or she's completely deceiving
even herself.

38:05.222 --> 38:07.808
Either way, it was just
attempted insurance fraud, right?

38:09.101 --> 38:11.311
Ju Hyun-su didn't start out
intending to commit murder either.

38:13.480 --> 38:15.816
It started with the insurance payout
from the car accident.

38:17.150 --> 38:19.861
His accident insurance got denied,
so he needed a scapegoat.

38:22.239 --> 38:23.532
And that was my sister.

38:25.700 --> 38:28.912
So you think Han Seol-ah likely received
a payout in the past as well?

38:30.539 --> 38:31.456
Probably.

38:56.481 --> 38:59.317
I heard Ms. Kim died
after an argument with Ms. Han.

38:59.901 --> 39:00.735
Really?

39:01.695 --> 39:04.364
I heard Ms. Han gave Ms. Kim
a really tough time.

39:28.346 --> 39:31.141
I sensed something might happen
from the moment you tore that painting.

39:32.350 --> 39:33.977
I can't blame her for wanting to die.

39:35.937 --> 39:37.314
I've kept quiet about this,

39:37.397 --> 39:40.859
but Ms. Kim often came to me in tears.

39:40.942 --> 39:42.068
Because of you.

39:43.570 --> 39:44.654
I see.

39:44.738 --> 39:47.240
Then why didn't you do a better job
comforting her?

39:47.324 --> 39:49.701
I guess she couldn't rely on you either.

39:51.995 --> 39:52.913
Whatever.

39:52.996 --> 39:54.831
What's important is public opinion.

39:56.124 --> 39:57.542
The real reason Kim Yun-ji died…

39:57.626 --> 39:59.502
Han Seol-ah constantly bullied Kim Yun-ji…

39:59.586 --> 40:02.005
Rumors about the chief auctioneer
replacement have been floating around…

40:02.088 --> 40:04.257
Ms. Han is Chair Kim's secret daughter?

40:04.341 --> 40:05.550
There's no way.

40:06.676 --> 40:08.094
If you want to sway public opinion,

40:08.178 --> 40:10.180
you should at least use multiple accounts.

40:11.431 --> 40:12.265
What?

40:13.099 --> 40:13.975
What did you say?

40:18.438 --> 40:19.481
Damn it.

40:19.981 --> 40:22.567
She's too damn observant.

40:23.818 --> 40:24.778
For goodness' sake.

40:36.039 --> 40:37.457
A bit higher, please.

40:42.629 --> 40:43.463
Okay.

40:44.047 --> 40:45.048
Next piece.

40:46.967 --> 40:47.842
That's good.

40:53.306 --> 40:54.140
Set the lighting to 20.

40:56.768 --> 40:57.602
Okay, next piece.

41:07.612 --> 41:10.448
-Let's take a ten-minute break.
-Okay.

41:17.664 --> 41:20.333
THE REAL REASON KIM YUN-JI DIED
RUMORS ABOUT CHIEF AUCTIONEER REPLACEMENT

41:22.252 --> 41:24.170
IS IT TRUE THAT MS. HAN IS QUITTING?

41:25.255 --> 41:26.339
What do you think?

41:28.508 --> 41:29.342
About what?

41:30.343 --> 41:33.263
I'm asking how much you can trust
your best friend, Han Seol-ah.

41:34.889 --> 41:36.308
Go back to work.

41:36.391 --> 41:38.018
She scares me now.

41:38.101 --> 41:39.936
I'm worried about you.

41:41.938 --> 41:45.025
Be honest.
You're suspecting her too, aren't you?

41:48.653 --> 41:49.487
Eun-hye.

41:50.780 --> 41:52.198
Seol-ah's the one

41:52.949 --> 41:54.367
who got you this internship.

41:56.036 --> 41:58.288
The scholarships
and training opportunities you got

41:58.371 --> 41:59.622
didn't just happen on their own.

42:03.043 --> 42:04.169
I never asked her for any of that.

42:04.252 --> 42:05.628
Who does she think she is?

42:06.212 --> 42:07.714
She considers us family.

42:07.797 --> 42:08.631
Family?

42:08.715 --> 42:11.634
She's just pretending to care about me
so she can use you.

42:11.718 --> 42:13.428
She's just keeping you around
to make you take photos.

42:13.511 --> 42:15.305
Watch what you say.

42:25.231 --> 42:26.441
This tastes good.

42:28.902 --> 42:32.072
You told me before

42:32.864 --> 42:34.491
that my mom getting money

42:35.158 --> 42:36.951
from me falling ill

42:37.619 --> 42:39.662
wouldn't make her happy,

42:41.247 --> 42:44.959
and that it'd just lead her
further down a bad path.

42:45.752 --> 42:47.712
If I tell the truth,

42:49.214 --> 42:51.174
what will happen to her?

42:52.550 --> 42:53.885
Will she get taken away?

42:59.849 --> 43:00.850
Chae-rin.

43:02.727 --> 43:04.604
The only person who can stop your mom

43:05.480 --> 43:06.356
is you.

43:07.941 --> 43:10.443
And I want to protect you

43:11.861 --> 43:13.154
so you won't hurt anymore.

43:17.283 --> 43:18.952
I'm sorry I couldn't protect you sooner.

43:26.084 --> 43:27.293
I'm fuming.

43:27.377 --> 43:29.587
How much time do you think
Chae-rin's mom will serve?

43:29.671 --> 43:32.590
Can't people like her
just be locked up for good?

43:32.674 --> 43:33.925
What kind of mother is she?

43:35.135 --> 43:37.262
I'm glad Chae-rin finally spoke up,

43:38.513 --> 43:39.848
but I'm not sure about this.

43:41.433 --> 43:42.767
No matter how terrible a mom is,

43:43.643 --> 43:45.061
a child would still miss her.

43:46.271 --> 43:48.523
But still,
we couldn't just leave her like that.

43:48.606 --> 43:49.607
We had to save her.

43:49.691 --> 43:51.860
Did we really save her though?

43:51.943 --> 43:53.862
At least we saved her from the worst.

43:54.863 --> 43:57.574
The world's a crazy place.
All this over money.

43:58.783 --> 44:00.994
I've requested her foster care
and medical support,

44:01.077 --> 44:02.245
so make sure to follow up on it.

44:02.328 --> 44:04.038
I've already prepared
the necessary documents.

44:10.003 --> 44:11.045
Hello, this is Cha Woo-seok.

44:11.754 --> 44:14.966
Mr. Cha, this is the Insurance Fraud
Prevention Team at the KLIA.

44:15.049 --> 44:16.468
It's about your inquiry on Han Seol-ah.

44:16.551 --> 44:18.470
We found a policy
taken out with HA Life Insurance.

44:34.694 --> 44:36.529
SHOCK AS DOCTOR IN 30S DIES
IN SUSPECTED PROPOFOL SELF-INJECTION

44:37.363 --> 44:40.241
NFS REVEALS, "CAUSE OF DEATH WAS
PROPOFOL OVERDOSE, NO SIGNS OF FOUL PLAY"

44:42.494 --> 44:44.037
The doctor's name was Choi Young-ho.

44:44.120 --> 44:46.289
He had a whole life insurance policy
with HA Life Insurance,

44:46.372 --> 44:48.041
and the policy was set to pay out
500 million won

44:48.124 --> 44:50.627
to his then-partner, Han Seol-ah,
upon his death.

44:50.710 --> 44:52.545
His policy was canceled
before he died too.

44:53.129 --> 44:55.548
So she didn't
get this 500 million payout either?

44:57.383 --> 44:59.677
What's up with this woman?

45:00.345 --> 45:02.180
In any case, she didn't get the payout.

45:02.764 --> 45:05.808
Two people died after taking out
huge life insurance policies,

45:05.892 --> 45:07.310
and the beneficiary is the same person.

45:08.019 --> 45:09.812
As a former police captain,
do you not find it suspicious?

45:09.896 --> 45:12.565
That's why it's even less of our concern,

45:12.649 --> 45:15.109
unless the police take an interest in it.

45:15.193 --> 45:18.112
Jeez, you've become a corporate man
through and through.

45:19.364 --> 45:20.949
Hand this over to Detective Gong.

45:21.032 --> 45:23.451
Don't bother with things
that don't count for your performance.

45:24.994 --> 45:25.828
Hey, Cha-cha.

45:27.205 --> 45:28.498
Cha-cha!

45:30.208 --> 45:33.336
I don't know why
this reminds me of that movie.

45:38.925 --> 45:39.884
What are you doing?

45:47.433 --> 45:49.060
Don't you know Basic Instinct, Mr. Koo?

45:49.143 --> 45:52.605
Maybe Han Seol-ah is like Sharon Stone
in Basic Instinct.

45:52.689 --> 45:53.898
She uses her incredible beauty

45:53.982 --> 45:55.942
to seduce men
into taking out insurance policies

45:56.025 --> 45:57.860
before killing them without mercy!

46:04.409 --> 46:05.702
Should I just kill him?

46:08.079 --> 46:09.455
An SIU investigator?

46:09.539 --> 46:10.915
ION MENTAL CLINIC

46:10.999 --> 46:14.335
I'm not sure why I need to disclose
a deceased person's personal life.

46:15.837 --> 46:16.671
You're not even with the police.

46:18.214 --> 46:20.258
Then do you know who Han Seol-ah is?

46:22.760 --> 46:24.596
We have to maintain
doctor-patient confidentiality--

46:24.679 --> 46:26.472
So she was a patient here.

46:28.516 --> 46:30.685
In any case, I have nothing to tell you.

46:50.079 --> 46:50.913
Hello.

46:55.835 --> 46:58.379
Man, I'm hungry.

47:07.847 --> 47:08.890
Ms. Kim Mi-yeon?

47:10.767 --> 47:13.394
You know something about Ms. Han Seol-ah
and Dr. Choi Young-ho, don't you?

47:17.065 --> 47:18.232
I need a few minutes of your time.

47:22.528 --> 47:23.446
It'll cost you.

47:33.706 --> 47:34.874
Depression?

47:37.627 --> 47:39.253
I guess she was hurting badly

47:39.837 --> 47:41.214
after breaking up with her boyfriend.

47:45.593 --> 47:48.805
Are you saying
she dated someone before Mr. Choi?

47:49.389 --> 47:50.223
Are you kidding me?

47:50.807 --> 47:53.601
Of course, she dated someone before him.
She's gorgeous.

47:54.227 --> 47:57.605
Dr. Choi was so head over heels for her
that he even dumped his girlfriend.

48:02.694 --> 48:03.528
Anyway,

48:03.611 --> 48:06.531
an old heartbreak
is healed through new love.

48:06.614 --> 48:08.408
It's one of those cliché stories.

48:08.491 --> 48:11.869
But I guess she failed at healing,
seeing how things turned out for Dr. Choi.

48:15.748 --> 48:16.708
Then, by any chance,

48:17.625 --> 48:21.087
do you know anything more
about Han Seol-ah's previous boyfriend?

48:22.380 --> 48:23.297
He died.

48:24.215 --> 48:25.675
I think it was somewhere
in the Middle East.

48:25.758 --> 48:28.094
I heard he died in a terrorist attack.

48:30.763 --> 48:31.848
Are you sure he's dead?

48:32.765 --> 48:33.850
Yes.

48:33.933 --> 48:35.226
I mean, it's uncommon.

48:35.309 --> 48:37.019
A terrorist attack in the Middle East.

48:50.241 --> 48:52.577
HAN SEOL-AH MEETING WITH CHAIR KIM,
AUCTION TEAM AFTERNOON MEETING

48:54.245 --> 48:55.496
HAN SEOL-AH BUSINESS TRIP

49:01.878 --> 49:04.005
LEASE SIGNING FOR LUEN PALACE UNIT 702

49:06.174 --> 49:08.718
Did you know Kim Yun-ji went to see
Yoon Seung-jae at his restaurant?

49:08.801 --> 49:10.136
On the day before the accident, at that.

49:12.597 --> 49:13.973
Why did those two meet?

49:17.518 --> 49:19.854
LEASE SIGNING FOR LUEN PALACE UNIT 702

49:28.905 --> 49:30.072
You're still here?

49:32.074 --> 49:32.992
Yeah.

49:34.494 --> 49:35.369
What are you doing?

49:36.370 --> 49:39.165
Oh, I was just organizing some files.

49:40.291 --> 49:42.460
What brings you here at this hour?

49:45.922 --> 49:47.340
I wanted to ask you something.

49:50.343 --> 49:53.429
Seung-jae once mentioned
that he took out a life insurance policy…

49:55.723 --> 49:57.475
and named you as the beneficiary.

49:59.936 --> 50:01.062
By any chance…

50:04.190 --> 50:05.399
did you receive the payout?

50:08.903 --> 50:10.321
Why do you ask?

50:13.115 --> 50:14.492
Tell me. I need to know.

50:17.745 --> 50:19.205
Come on, not you too.

50:21.707 --> 50:22.583
Did you…

50:25.002 --> 50:25.878
really love…

50:27.338 --> 50:28.422
Seung-jae?

50:38.683 --> 50:39.517
Seol-ah.

50:40.059 --> 50:42.478
What do you want me to say?

50:43.062 --> 50:45.064
Don't you think
you're being too cruel to me?

50:45.690 --> 50:46.732
No, I didn't mean--

50:46.816 --> 50:47.692
Of all people,

50:49.151 --> 50:50.570
I thought you were on my side.

50:53.739 --> 50:55.283
This is all our friendship
amounts to, huh?

51:20.141 --> 51:22.768
NONGHYUP LIFE INSURANCE

51:22.852 --> 51:24.520
INSURANCE FOR THE ONES YOU LOVE

51:56.177 --> 51:59.805
YOON SEUNG-JAE, CHOI YOUNG-HO,
A THIRD MAN?

52:02.016 --> 52:04.060
HAN SEOL-AH

52:26.165 --> 52:28.918
"TERRORIST BOMB ATTACK IN SYRIA
KILLS KOREAN MAN"

52:31.337 --> 52:32.213
1 KOREAN AID WORKER KILLED

52:32.296 --> 52:34.173
On the 14th in Raqqa, Syria,

52:34.256 --> 52:37.218
a terrorist attack was carried out
by an armed group called IS,

52:37.301 --> 52:39.720
claiming the life of a Korean aid worker

52:39.804 --> 52:41.889
and adding to the grief of this tragedy.

52:41.973 --> 52:46.644
The attack took place in an area
controlled by IS-affiliated militants,

52:46.727 --> 52:51.232
and reports say a powerful explosion
killed dozens of people.

52:52.775 --> 52:56.237
THE DECEASED WAS A KOREAN NGO WORKER
PROVIDING HUMANITARIAN AID…

52:56.821 --> 52:58.572
They consigned it under my name?

52:58.656 --> 53:01.826
Yes, they insisted
that it be delivered to you.

53:11.210 --> 53:12.545
It's called…

53:13.462 --> 53:15.172
An Orphan from Syria.

54:38.172 --> 54:39.048
Nice painting.

54:42.968 --> 54:44.887
Unauthorized personnel
aren't allowed in here.

54:44.970 --> 54:45.971
Please leave.

54:49.642 --> 54:50.643
Seven years ago,

54:51.769 --> 54:54.063
there was a woman who had a boyfriend.

54:55.022 --> 54:57.066
The man worked
for an international relief organization

54:57.149 --> 54:59.068
that often went into
dangerous conflict zones.

55:00.861 --> 55:04.156
He took out a life insurance policy
for the woman he loved.

55:04.240 --> 55:05.324
The policy

55:06.117 --> 55:08.285
was set to pay out 200 million won
upon his death.

55:12.039 --> 55:14.250
He died in a terrorist attack in Syria.

55:19.004 --> 55:22.007
But the woman
couldn't collect the payout. Why?

55:23.968 --> 55:26.428
Because he suddenly canceled the policy.

55:28.472 --> 55:30.099
She must've been devastated.

55:31.225 --> 55:32.393
She lost her lover

55:33.352 --> 55:34.562
and the payout.

55:36.355 --> 55:39.733
Following the incident,
she became depressed and sought therapy.

55:41.694 --> 55:44.488
But who knows if she was
actually depressed or just pretending?

55:46.991 --> 55:47.867
And this is when

55:47.950 --> 55:50.035
a certain psychiatrist
makes his appearance.

55:50.119 --> 55:53.038
He fell in love with the woman
while trying to help her heal.

55:53.122 --> 55:54.456
ION MENTAL CLINIC
DIRECTOR CHOI YOUNG-HO

55:55.916 --> 55:59.003
He also took out a life insurance policy
and named her the beneficiary.

55:59.587 --> 56:00.838
But a few days before his suicide,

56:01.714 --> 56:02.923
he canceled the policy.

56:05.676 --> 56:07.803
The restaurant CEO
who got into an accident on the river

56:07.887 --> 56:09.680
also canceled his policy before he died.

56:14.101 --> 56:17.438
The woman lost three men
but gained nothing.

56:19.857 --> 56:22.568
But unlike her,
I gained something from these three cases.

56:24.278 --> 56:25.905
If you love Han Seol-ah…

56:28.741 --> 56:29.742
you die.

56:32.077 --> 56:33.078
And that's a fact.

56:41.921 --> 56:44.590
I'm sure those men wanted to save
the deeply hurt woman.

56:44.673 --> 56:47.051
You see, men tend to go blind

56:47.134 --> 56:49.053
once they fall in love.

56:49.136 --> 56:52.097
That's why they gave their all to her,
even their lives.

56:54.516 --> 56:55.601
In those men's eyes,

56:57.019 --> 56:59.104
she must've seemed like such a pitiful,

57:00.564 --> 57:02.274
helpless woman.

57:08.530 --> 57:10.032
Then, in your eyes,

57:10.950 --> 57:13.118
how does that woman appear right now?

57:30.344 --> 57:31.303
I'm not sure.

57:33.639 --> 57:34.723
I can't really see her.

57:47.987 --> 57:48.946
Can you see her now?

57:52.658 --> 57:54.201
That pitiful woman…

57:58.706 --> 58:00.958
Does she look like the kind of woman

58:01.917 --> 58:03.585
who wants to be saved by another man?

58:15.347 --> 58:17.391
You said anyone who loves me ends up dead.

58:18.350 --> 58:20.728
You talk as if
you know everything about me.

58:25.816 --> 58:27.484
Then tell me.

58:29.111 --> 58:30.612
Who's next?

58:32.156 --> 58:33.365
Next?

58:41.457 --> 58:43.500
The next man who'll fall in love…

58:47.546 --> 58:48.589
with Han Seol-ah.

59:07.066 --> 59:10.361
SPECIAL THANKS TO LEE ELIJAH
AND HA SEOKJIN FOR THEIR APPEARANCE

59:33.675 --> 59:35.594
The pain of becoming a mistress.

59:36.303 --> 59:38.972
The man who doesn't deliver
on his promise.

59:39.056 --> 59:40.849
What did you gain
from the deaths of those men?

59:41.308 --> 59:43.852
Does knowing that change anything?

59:45.020 --> 59:46.355
I think I know where it is.

59:48.982 --> 59:50.692
It felt like I was falling in love.

59:50.776 --> 59:53.821
So? Did you decide on your next man?

59:54.446 --> 59:57.324
Step aside if you don't want to cause
any misunderstandings.

59:58.992 --> 01:00:00.119
Who exactly are you?

01:00:01.203 --> 01:00:02.830
Why did you approach me?

01:00:05.791 --> 01:00:07.793
Subtitle: Jenny Kim
